						               													<description>A hidden roles card game game. One player plays as the NASTI agent the others are Foundation operatives. One random player chooses to secretly place either treasure or bombs in the Maltese Falcon. The players then use the swap cards to move the Maltese Falcon from player to player. At the end of the round the player who has the Maltese Falcon may or may not open it. If they choose to keep it closed they gain 1 victory point. If they open it and it is treasure they keep the highest for themself and share the other two out (between 1 and 3 victory points). If there are bombs inside they take the highest hit and give the lower two to the players either side (between -2 and -3 victory points). After 3 rounds whoever has the highest victory points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For now this is a playtesting copy of the new McGuffin.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
